  "designDecisions": [
    "In-memory singleton store (src/lib/store.ts) uses a module-level Map for users, clients, invoices, expenses — persists for server lifetime, auto-seeds with demo data so app is usable immediately on first load",
    "Cookie-based session auth: login sets an httpOnly cookie containing a signed userId; middleware.ts checks this cookie and redirects unauthenticated users away from dashboard routes",
    "A mock user (demo@example.com / password: demo) is seeded on startup with sample clients, invoices, and expenses so reviewers can explore a populated app instantly without registration",
    "Invoice numbering uses a configurable prefix (default INV-) plus a zero-padded auto-incrementing counter stored per user in the in-memory store",
    "All monetary calculations happen server-side in API routes using integer math (cents) to avoid floating-point errors; display layer formats with Intl.NumberFormat",
    "Currency list (50+ ISO currencies) is a static lookup in src/lib/currencies.ts — no external exchange rate API required for MVP; amounts are stored in the invoice's chosen currency",
    "Tax calculation is a simple percentage applied to the line-item subtotal; each invoice carries a single taxRate field for MVP simplicity, matching Phase 1 scope from the PRD",
    "Invoice PDF generation is deferred to a print-stylesheet approach: /invoice/[id] public page renders a printer-friendly layout; users hit Ctrl+P or browser Print to get a PDF — zero dependencies",
    "The public invoice view at /invoice/[id] is accessible without auth so freelancers can share a link with clients; it shows invoice details and simulates a 'Mark as Paid' button that calls PATCH /api/invoices/[id]/status",
    "Dashboard revenue chart uses an inline SVG bar chart built from raw data arrays — no charting library required, keeping bundle size minimal",
    "Tailwind CSS utility classes are used exclusively for styling with a cn() helper (clsx-style manual implementation in src/lib/utils.ts) — no shadcn/ui or other component libraries",
    "All UI components (Button, Input, Modal, Badge, Card, Table, Select, Textarea) are hand-built in src/components/ui/ using Tailwind only — consistent design tokens via className composition",
    "Middleware (src/middleware.ts) uses Next.js middleware config to protect all /dashboard/* and /api/* routes except /api/auth/*  and the public /invoice/* route",
    "Reports (P&L, aged receivables, tax summary) are computed on-demand in /api/reports by aggregating in-memory invoice and expense data — no pre-aggregation or background jobs needed at MVP scale",
    "Expense categories are a fixed enum (Software, Travel, Equipment, Marketing, Office, Professional Services, Other) stored as constants in src/types/index.ts to ensure UI consistency",
    "The app is structured with a Route Group (dashboard) layout that includes the Sidebar and TopBar, keeping auth pages (/login, /register) and the public invoice page outside this layout",
    "Responsive design is achieved via Tailwind breakpoint prefixes; Sidebar collapses to a hamburger menu on mobile using React local state, requiring no additional libraries",
    "Client archiving is a soft-delete (status: 'active' | 'archived') so invoice history is preserved; API filters return only active clients by default with an ?includeArchived=true opt-in"
